        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 8:43PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 842 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms in the vicinity of Cheraw, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chavistown and Wallace.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
